00:12:44.410 --> 00:12:47.320
the way that you're used to
working before Final Cut Pro HD.

00:12:47.320 --> 00:12:52.760
You shoot in a camera-native format
that is either HD cam or DVC Pro HD.

00:12:52.760 --> 00:12:55.200
These are the two standard
HD formats out there.

00:12:55.200 --> 00:12:57.950
HD cam is from Sony,
DVC Pro HD is from Panasonic,

00:12:57.950 --> 00:13:02.250
and they are the makers of the two
primary digital HD cameras in the world.

00:13:02.260 --> 00:13:05.010
You would then capture that into
Final Cut Pro using one of the

00:13:05.090 --> 00:13:07.770
cards that we mentioned earlier,
but you would capture it

00:13:07.770 --> 00:13:09.320
into an uncompressed space.

00:13:09.430 --> 00:13:10.400
Now that has made sense.

00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:13.480
In that process, you're effectively
decompressing the image,

00:13:13.480 --> 00:13:15.700
but you're not actually
adding anything to it.

00:13:15.750 --> 00:13:18.920
So what happens is a lot of
people missed out on the fact that

00:13:18.920 --> 00:13:20.780
HD tapes are not uncompressed.

00:13:20.780 --> 00:13:23.260
The footage that goes on
the tapes is just like DV.

00:13:23.260 --> 00:13:24.380
DV is not uncompressed.

00:13:24.380 --> 00:13:26.120
It's a 4 or 5 to 1 compression.

00:13:26.120 --> 00:13:29.010
So you have a massive amount of
compression that's happening in the

00:13:29.010 --> 00:13:30.710
camera before it ever goes to tape.

00:13:30.840 --> 00:13:33.540
So if you take this HD cam or
DVC Pro HD tape and you capture

00:13:33.540 --> 00:13:36.960
it into an uncompressed space,
you're not gaining anything.

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:40.560
You're actually taking that,
moving it into an uncompressed space.

00:13:40.560 --> 00:13:43.010
And by the time you get back to tape,
you will have suffered

00:13:43.010 --> 00:13:43.990
a generational loss.

00:13:44.060 --> 00:13:46.490
So the next step in here, of course,
is to go back to tape,

00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:48.760
so into your camera native HD,
and that recompress,

00:13:48.760 --> 00:13:51.350
and there's where your
generational loss is happening.

00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:53.140
